//! @mainpage n65 Toolchain
//!
//! @brief Developer documentation for the n65 compiler toolchain.
//!
//! The tree is organized around small command-line tools that hand off plain
//! intermediate artifacts: n65cc compiles `.n` source to assembly, n65asm
//! assembles source to Intel HEX or o65 objects, n65ld links o65 inputs,
//! n65ar packages object archives, and n65driver coordinates the tools for
//! normal command-line use. Runtime support code and the simulator live beside
//! those tools because they are installed or used by end-to-end builds, but the
//! public tool modules below are the primary entry points for maintainers.
//!
//! Tool modules:
//! - @ref compiler
//! - @ref assembler
//! - @ref linker
//! - @ref archiver
//! - @ref driver
//!
//! Supporting modules:
//! - @ref runtime
//! - @ref simulator
//!
//! @defgroup compiler Compiler
//! @brief Sources for n65cc, including parsing, semantic checks, ABI metadata,
//! AST transforms, and assembly emission.
//!
//! @defgroup assembler Assembler
//! @brief Sources for n65asm, including lexer/parser glue, instruction
//! selection, relaxation, symbol management, listings, Intel HEX, and o65
//! object emission.
//!
//! @defgroup linker Linker
//! @brief Sources for n65ld, including o65/archive loading, configuration,
//! relocation, layout, map output, and ABI metadata validation.
//!
//! @defgroup archiver Archiver
//! @brief Sources for n65ar, the simple NAR65 archive reader/writer used by
//! the linker.
//!
//! @defgroup driver Driver
//! @brief Sources for n65driver, the orchestration front-end that invokes the
//! compiler, assembler, linker, and archiver with installed search paths.
//!
//! @defgroup runtime Runtime support
//! @brief Runtime headers and support sources used by compiled programs.
//!
//! @defgroup simulator Simulator
//! @brief Simulator support used by n65sim for end-to-end execution checks.
